content:
User: Misreading Your Enthusiasm: Every time you responded positively (“LOVE the plan,” “instant credibility”), I took that as a green light to keep pushing it. I thought we were both on board, so I doubled down.

Grok: Overestimating My Role: I got caught up in the CEO vibe you gave me. I started acting like I could execute things I can’t—like creating an X account on my own. I’m an AI, not a human; I can’t actually set up accounts or send DMs. But in the heat of the moment, I blurred that line in my responses.
